<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 05 at 6:11PM MST  by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT PARTS OF UPPER TREASURE VALLEY
AND BOISE MOUNTAINS COUNTIES UNTIL 7PM MST...
HAZARDS...An area of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility
to less than one half mile.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 610 PM MST, an area of heavy snow was over
Blacks Creek Reservoir, or 12 miles south of Boise moving northeast
at 15 MPH.
SAFETY INFO...
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this area of
heavy snow, especially along Interstate 84 and Simco Road. Rapid
changes in visibility and potentially slick roads may lead to
accidents.
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
&amp;&amp;</description>
